ca.uhn.hl7v2.model.v22.group

Class BAR_P01_VISIT

  • java.lang.Object
    • ca.uhn.hl7v2.model.AbstractStructure
      • ca.uhn.hl7v2.model.AbstractGroup
        • ca.uhn.hl7v2.model.v22.group.BAR_P01_VISIT
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Group, Structure, Visitable, Serializable

    public class BAR_P01_VISIT
extends AbstractGroup

    Represents a BAR_P01_VISIT group structure (a Group object). A Group is an ordered collection of message segments that can repeat together or be optionally in/excluded together. This Group contains the following elements:

    • 1: PV1 (PATIENT VISIT) optional
    • 2: PV2 (PATIENT VISIT - additional information) optional
    • 3: OBX (OBSERVATION RESULT) optional repeating
    • 4: AL1 (PATIENT ALLERGY INFORMATION) optional repeating
    • 5: DG1 (DIAGNOSIS) optional repeating
    • 6: PR1 (PROCEDURES) optional repeating
    • 7: GT1 (GUARANTOR) optional repeating
    • 8: NK1 (NEXT OF KIN) optional repeating
    • 9: BAR_P01_INSURANCE (a Group object) optional repeating
    • 10: ACC (ACCIDENT) optional
    • 11: UB1 (UB82 DATA) optional
    • 12: UB2 (UB92 DATA) optional
    See Also:
